			<div class="blog-faq">
				<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Is plastic surgery really safe?</h3>
					<p>Yes, when performed by a board-certified plastic surgeon in an accredited facility, plastic surgery is generally safe. Like all surgical procedures, it carries some risks, but these are significantly reduced when you choose a qualified, experienced surgeon and follow all pre- and post-operative instructions carefully.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>At what age can I get plastic surgery?</h3>
					<p>The appropriate age depends on the procedure. Some procedures like rhinoplasty can be performed once facial growth is complete (around age 16-18), while others like facelifts are more common among patients in their 40s and beyond. Age alone does not determine candidacy — overall health and individual goals are more important factors.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Will people be able to tell if I've had plastic surgery?</h3>
					<p>When performed by a skilled surgeon, plastic surgery results are natural-looking and subtle. The goal is to enhance your features, not to create an artificial appearance. Most people will notice that you look refreshed and more confident, but they may not be able to pinpoint the exact change.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Can men get plastic surgery?</h3>
					<p>Absolutely. Male plastic surgery is growing in popularity. Common procedures for men include gynecomastia surgery, rhinoplasty, liposuction, and facelifts. Dr. Johar has extensive experience treating male patients and understanding their unique aesthetic goals.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Is plastic surgery only for cosmetic reasons?</h3>
					<p>No. Plastic surgery includes both cosmetic and reconstructive procedures. Reconstructive procedures include breast reconstruction after mastectomy, cleft lip and palate repair, burn treatment, and reconstruction after trauma. The specialty is much broader than cosmetic enhancement alone.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How long does recovery from plastic surgery take?</h3>
					<p>Recovery time varies by procedure. Many procedures require one to four weeks of downtime. Full results may take several weeks to months to become apparent as swelling subsides, but most patients can resume normal activities well before then.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Will my insurance cover plastic surgery?</h3>
					<p>Insurance may cover reconstructive procedures that are deemed medically necessary, such as breast reconstruction after mastectomy or repair of congenital deformities. Purely cosmetic procedures are typically not covered. During your consultation, we can discuss payment options and EMI plans to make your procedure more accessible.</p>
				</div>
